<FIRST>r a PM-APAppointment     09-27 0098</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0100</SECOND>
<HEAD>AP Correspondent Named in Carbondale, Ill.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARBONDALE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shera Gross, a newswoman in the
Nashville bureau of The Associated Press for 18 months, has been
named AP's correspondent in Carbondale.
   The appointment was announced Tuesday by Chicago Chief of Bureau
James Wilson.
   Ms. Gross, 25, is a native of Nashville and a graduate of the
University of Tennessee. She worked for United Press International
in Jackson, Miss., prior to joining the AP in Nashville.
   In Carbondale she succeeds Paul de la Garza, who has been named
night supervisor in the Chicago bureau.
</TEXT>
