<HEAD>Poindexter To Subpoena Reagan And Bush</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush and former President Reagan
will be subpoenaed in the Iran-Contra trial of former national
security adviser John Poindexter, according to Poindexter.
   In court documents made available Tuesday, Poindexter said he
needs the records for his defense against criminal charges.
   Reagan's notes will reflect that he authorized some activities
for which Poindexter was indicted, Poindexter's lawyers have said.
   Poindexter said vice presidential records at the national
archives have yet to be processed and that to date no personal
diary from Bush's tenure as vice president has been discovered.
   The former national security adviser is charged with one count
of conspiracy, two counts of obstructing Congress and two counts of
making false statements in the Iran-Contra affair.
