<HEAD>Jackie Mason Says Dinkins Doesn't Merit Jewish Support</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Comic Jackie Mason says Jewish guilt could help
Democrat David Dinkins become mayor, the Village Voice reported
today.
   ``There is a sick Jewish problem of voting for a black man no
matter how unfit he is for the job,'' the weekly quoted the
rabbi-turned-comedian as saying.
   The remarks were heard by a Voice writer who said he sat with
the star of television's ``Chicken Soup'' at an Italian Welfare
