<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--LSD     09-27 0125</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--LSD,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>Customs Agents Seize LSD Smuggled in Gorbachev Stickers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUESSELDORF, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Customs agents arrested two
West Germans trying to smuggle in LSD soaked into stickers bearing
the image of Soviet leader Mikhail S. Gorbachev, authorities said
Wednesday.
   Agents at the Elten-Emmerich border crossing near Holland found
130 sheets of LSD-treated paper with Gorbachev's image stamped on
to look like decals, according to the regional customs office.
   Two West German workers with the Civilian Service, the
government's alternative to compulsory military service, were taken
into custody after a search of their car turned up the contraband
Monday.
   The Gorbachev stamps were similar to previous drug-smuggling
attempts in which pictures of Batman, Goofy and E.T. have been used
to disguise LSD doses.
</TEXT>
