<HEAD>Archbishop of Ottawa Resigns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pope John Paul II on Wednesday accepted the
resignation of Archbishop Joseph-Aurele Plourde of Ottawa, the
Vatican announced.
   The coadjutor of the archdiocese, Monsignor Marcel Andre
Gervais, automatically takes over as archbishop, the Vatican said.
   Plourde in January turns 75, the age at which bishops must
submit their resignations.
