<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--UnluckyTrain     09-27 0136</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Unlucky Train,0140</SECOND>
<HEAD>The Little Train That Couldn't</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERGEN, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Norwegian State Railroad's luck was on
the wrong track this week.
   The trouble started Monday when sparks from a bonfire lit by
railroad workers set fire to a wooden structure used to keep snow
off the tracks.
   Workers rolled out fire hoses only to find that a defective
coupling had cut water pressure. They fixed the coupling, but the
old hoses ruptured when the pressure increased.
   The blazing structure then collapsed onto the tracks, and the
heat warped the rails.
   The newspaper Bergens Tidene said about 1,000 passengers were
stranded for hours in the mountains outside Bergen and finally put
onto buses.
   ``We had certain technical problems,'' traffic manager Lars
Bjoerndal was quoted as saying.
   No one was injured in the mishaps.
</TEXT>
