<HEAD>Etna Continues To Spew Lava, Ash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CATANIA, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mount Etna lit up the sky early Wednesday
with fire and fountains of lava spraying from the southeast crater
of Europe's most active volcano.
   The volcano also spewed ash that blew six miles west toward the
small towns of Milo, Fornazzo and Giarre, said Dr. Gianni Fazzetta
of the International Volcanology Institute of Catania.
   The volcano is in an active phase of the eruption that began
Sept. 11, Fazzetta said. Officials called the eruption spectacular
but said it poses no threat to people.
