<FIRST>r a AM-DestituteWoman     09-27 0354</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Destitute Woman,350</SECOND>
<HEAD>Suspected Prostitute Goes to Grave Unidentified</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FAIRFAX, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who died of a heart attack in jail
before she could be arraigned on a prostitution charge will be
buried in a pauper's grave because Fairfax County authorities could
not identify her.
   The woman left a trail that included 38 aliases, five Social
Security numbers, four claimed dates of birth, and at least 28
arrests for crimes from bank robbery to drug possession over 15
years, according to FBI files.
   ``We will never know who she was,'' said Sheriff M. Wayne
Huggins. ``We worked on it for two weeks, but it became one of
those situations where the more you looked the stranger it got.
   ``It just makes me sad. Sad to look at this life and see what a
tragedy it was,'' Huggins said.
   Her aliases included Catherine Ann Kaine, Katherine Ann Caine _
Candy Caine for short _ when she was arrested Aug. 31 at a motel on
a prostitution charge.
   She died Sept. 5 before her arraignment.
   Police believe she was 34, but was emaciated, worn and looked at
least 50. When the tall blonde was arrested, she had fresh needle
marks on her arms from a drug habit, police said.
   The woman told police she was married, but didn't leave behind
any emergency telephone numbers.
   ``There seemed to be a lot of information there, but we just
couldn't really find anyone who knew a lot about her,'' Huggins
said.
   The woman, who was cremated, will be buried by the county social
services department in potter's field, the Fairfax City Cemetery,
Huggins said.
   During the investigation, one man surfaced who claimed to have
married her in a $10 ceremony in Las Vegas, but investigators
couldn't find any records and allege he was actually in the
prostitution business with her.
   Another man said he was her brother, but authorities doubted
him. That man said she was from Roanoke, but no leads were found
there.
   Huggins last hope was in Chicago, where she was first arrested
for prositution 15 years ago. That was also a futile search.
</TEXT>
