<FIRST>r i AM-Venezuela-OilAccident     09-27 0141</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Venezuela-Oil Accident,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>4 Americans Killed in Venezuelan Gas Explosion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gas explosion in a well killed four
American workers Wednesday morning in northeastern Venezuela, the
state oil company Petroleos de Venezuela announced.
   The four men, employed by firms contracted by the state oil
company's affiliate Corpoven, were helping repair an exploratory
petroleum well in Monagas state.
   According to news reports, Don McCormick and David Hernandez of
the Otis Company and Don Whitehead of Royal Oil Tools died
instantly in a sudden blaze caused by a gas leak as they extracted
a pipe from the well.
   The fourth victim, Ricky Johnson, also of Otis, suffered severe
burns and died a short time after the 8:45 a.m. accident at a
nearby hospital.
   Corpoven said the accident is under investigation.
   Hometowns of the victims were not immediately available.
