and assaulted a Swede outside a Stockholm night club, causing a
severe eye injury. Later that evening, he beat another Swedish
youth, it said.
   The Briton admitted the first beating, but denied the second,
although several witnesses identified him, the national news agency
TT said.
   More than 200 English and Swedish supporters were arrested in
brawls before and after the match, which ended in a 0-0 draw.
