<FIRST>r f PM-TreasuryAuction     09-27 0089</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Treasury Auction,0094</SECOND>
<HEAD>T-Bill Yields Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on two-year Treasury notes rose in
Tuesday's auction to the highest level since May.
   The average yield was 8.39 percent, up from 8.37 percent at the
last auction, Aug. 22.
   It was the highest rate since two-year notes averaged 8.84
percent May 25. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 8]
percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,997.30.
   A total of $9.75 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$26.8 billion.
</TEXT>
