<HEAD>RJR Nabisco Makes Its Move From Atlanta to New York Official</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   RJR Nabisco Inc. announced today it is setting up
headquarters on the Avenue of the Americas in New York, making the
company's move out of Atlanta official.
   RJR Nabisco said in April it was planning to move from its
suburban Atlanta headquarters to New York, and the company's top
executives have been operating out of temporary offices in New York
for several months while maintaining an office here.
   The tobacco and food giant moved to Atlanta from its longtime
home in Winston-Salem, N.C., in 1987. The company was acquired by
Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &amp; Co. in a record-setting $24.5 billion
debt-financed buyout that was finalized earlier this year.
   ``For the job we have ahead of us, New York is the place to
be,'' said RJR Nabisco Chairman Louis V. Gerstner Jr. ``We plan to
sink roots here (in New York).''
   The company said it had signed a 10-year lease for 86,400 square
feet of office space. The space is being renovated for occupancy
next June.
