Inc.
   Wheat had opened higher as prices were supported by Egypt's
tender for 500,000 metric tons of the U.S. commodity, and on news
that the Agriculture Department has targeted the African country
for 1 million metric tons of export bonus wheat, analysts said.
   But wheat prices turned lower due to a noticeable lack of
commercial buying, they said.
