<FIRST>r f AM-ElectronicsSuit     09-27 0155</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Electronics Suit,0163</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kollmorgen-Vernitron Merger Off; Kollmorgen Files Suit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kollmorgen Corp. filed a lawsuit
Wednesday against Venitron Corp. for backing out of a $320 million
merger agreement.
   Vernitron had cited ``adverse changes in the financial
performance of Kollmorgen'' when it announced last week it was
abandoning its $25-a-share acquisition of Kollmorgen.
   The two electronics companies had entered into the buyout
agreement on April 30, and the deal was scheduled to close Saturday.
   Kollmorgen filed suit in state Superior Court in Stamford,
alleging ``clear and willful breach'' of the deal and seeking
unspecified damages.
   The company said its board of directors formally terminated the
Vernitron agreement on Tuesday and approved a restructuring plan
that includes the sale of certain assets.
   Kollmorgen, based in Stamford, makes electrical and optical
equipment.
   Vernitron, based in Deer Park, N.Y., and the smaller of the two
companies, produces electronic components for aerospace, defense
and communications industries.
</TEXT>
