<HEAD>What's For Sale in Retailing</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Stores For Sale, Bjt</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Here are facts about several U.S. store chains that have been
put up for sale in the U.S. retailing industry:
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>OWNED BY BAT INDUSTRIES PLC</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Breuners _ A furniture business with 17 retail stores and 44
rental centers operating in Arizona, California and Nevada. It is
based in San Ramon, Calif.
   Ivey's _ A specialty department store with 23 units in North
Carolina, South Carolina and Florida. It is based in Charlotte, N.C.
   Marshall Field's _ A department store chain appealing mainly to
affluent buyers, with stores in Illinois, Ohio, Texas and
Wisconsin. The main store of the 130-year-old retailer is located
on State Street in Chicago and is one of the city's landmarks.
   Saks Fifth Avenue _ A high-fashion specialty department store
chain of 46 stores dotted around the country. Its flagship store in
New York is on Manhattan's famed Fifth Avenue.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>OWNED BY CAMPEAU CORP.</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Bloomingdale's _ A department store chain widely associated with
the latest fashion trends and admired for its merchandising
methods. Bloomingdale's, a unit of Campeau's Federated Department
Stores Inc., is based in New York. It runs 17 stores in
Connecticut, Florida, Massachusetts, Maryland, New Jersey, New
York, Pennsylvania, Texas, Virginia.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>OWNED BY MAY DEPARTMENT STORES CO.</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Caldor _ A general merchandise discounter operating about 120
stores in the Northeast.
   Venture _ A general merchandise discounter operating about 73
stores in the Midwest.
</TEXT>
