<HEAD>Eds: Updates with closing prices throughout.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CHET CURRIER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices finished mixed Wednesday in a
session marked by pressure on some technology issues but strength
in other blue chips.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, up about 10 in early
trading and down about 4 at midafternoon, closed with a 9.12 gain
at 2,673.06.
   Declining issues outnumbered advances by nearly 4 to 3 in
nationwide tra Stock Exchange-listed stocks, with
626 up, 826 down and 514 unchanged.
   Volume on the floor of the Big Board came to 158.40 million
shares, against 158.35 million in the previous sessioding of New Yorkn.
Nationwide,
consolidated volume in NYSE-listed issues, including trades in
those stocks on regional exchanges and in the over-the-counter
market, totaled 185.41 million shares.
   The market had to contend with some renewed weakness in the
dollar and an accompanying rise in credit-market interest rates.
   Prices of long-term government bonds declined slightly,
increasing their yields to the 8.25 percent-8.30 percent range.
   Stocks also were weighed down by International Business Machines
Corp.'s disclosure that it expects earnings for the third quarter
to come in well below current estimates by analysts.
   IBM shares fell 6 to 111{. Elsewhere in the technology sector,
Digital Equipment dropped 1] to 93|;  of single-country closed end funds,
investment companies
that special in the securities of a given foreign nation or region
of the globe, had another volatile day after their recent runup
punctuated by bouts of profit-taking.
   Austria Fund rose 1} to 14\, and Brazil Fund gained } to 12~,
but Spain Fund tumbled 9 to 29}; Malaysia Fund lost 2[ to 13\;
Germany Fund dropped 1 to 14, and Thai Fund was down 2\ at 24\.
   As measured by Wilshire Associates' index of more than 5,000
actively traded stocks, the market increased $6.10 billion, or 0.18
percent, in value.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks added
.35 to 191.82.
   Standard &amp; Poor's industrial index rose .87 to 393.88, and S&amp;P's
500-stock composite index was up .77 at 345.10.
   The NASDAQ composite index for the over-the-counter market
slipped .07 to 467.77. At the American Stock Exchange, the market
value index closed at 383.04, up .85.
