<HEAD>Richman Retires From Philip Morris</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John M. Richman, vice chairman of Philip Morris
Cos. and chairman and chief executive officer of Kraft General
Foods, plans to retire at the end of the year, the company
announced Wednesday.
   The company said that Michael A. Miles, president and chief
operating officer of Kraft, will succeed Richman as chief executive
officer immediately. Miles is also expected to be nominated as vice
chairman, it said.
   Richman, who joined Kraft in 1954 in the company's legal
department, was elected Kraft chairman in 1979.
   He was named vice chairman of Philip Morris in 1988 after the
company's $12.9 billion takeover of Kraft that year.
   Richman is leaving the consumer products giant to become counsel
to the New York law firm Wachtell, Lipton, Rosen &amp; Katz, Philip
Morris said.
