<SECOND>AM-Food Label Hearings, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0146,0215</SECOND>
<HEAD>FDA Schedules Hearings on Food Labeling</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS grafs 6-7, beginning `_Nov. 1 ... ' to CORRECT topics of
hearings, which had been reversed. Picks up penultimate graf, `_Dec. 13
... '. Also moving on general news wires.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Food and Drug Administration has scheduled
hearings in Chicago, San Antonio, Seattle and Atlanta to let
consumers and others recommend changes in food labeling.
   The FDA is considering revising food labeling regulations
concerning health claims made by manufacturers, nutrition content
of food, ingredients, descriptive terms used on labels and label
format.
   Each hearing will focus on a different aspect of labeling, but
comments on any or all of the specific issues will be accepted at
the hearings, the FDA said.
   The hearings will be held:
   _Oct. 16 in Chicago on nutrition information that should be
included on food labels.
   _Nov. 1 in Seattle on health messages on food labels.
   _Dec. 7 in San Antonio on ingredient labeling and food
descriptions.
   _Dec. 13 in Atlanta on formats for nutrition labeling.
   Consumers, food retailers and manufacturers, health care
providers and others interested in food labeling who want to
testify should contact the FDA in the cities where the hearings are
scheduled.
</TEXT>
